This paper discusses the use of evolutionary algorithms for dynamic optimization problems, which are commonly studied in the field of computational intelligence (cs.NE). The paper also provides theoretical explanations for the importance of populations in dynamic optimization, which is relevant to the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the relationship between population size and algorithm performance, which is relevant to the field of control systems (cs.SY) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
